President Trump made remarks in the Roosevelt Room about the importance of protecting and reforming the care for veterans. He expressed his belief that veterans have not been treated fairly and emphasized his commitment to changing that. The President also mentioned a meeting he was having with some individuals involved in the reform of the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA). Secretary David Shulkin thanked the President for his support and mentioned the passage of an accountability bill by the House. President Trump also briefly mentioned a meeting he had with congressmen regarding healthcare and expressed confidence in the future of healthcare reform.